<br>
And someone else doing a quest with the NPC will not matter unless they happen to JUST give the 3 gems you were going to.  If they do a different quest, or even complete the same quest (both armor and gems) it won't matter one bit.   You can even hand in 2 pieces of armor, log your alt, turn in the 3 gems for one, then the 3 gems for the other and you get both pieces.<br>
<br>
And there isn't a level limit, if you get the quest text from the NPC (by having the right faction) you get the piece.  My level 40 warrior has Kael armor using pieces looted in ToV. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udrakinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drakinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/02 11:15:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4636.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: MQing Thurg armor with an alt</span><hr size=1> hehe, i usually do just that, give my 3 gems first then hand in the armor right afterwards<br>
